      "description": "Block agents from writing user-approved markers into file content (only the project owner can approve eslint-disable approvals with the JC: prefix). The path-scoped scoped_blocks are write-time fingerprints per PDR-044 §Innate immunity. Two kinds: (literal) the hedging-vocabulary trip-list — language that means 'I know the rule applies, but this situation is special' rejected on doctrine surfaces (PDRs, plans, ADRs, governance), with doctrine-defining surfaces excluded so principles.md, distilled.md, PDR-043 and PDR-044 may catalogue the words they forbid; (regex) the SHA-in-permanent-doc fingerprint — 7- to 40-character hex tokens with at least one a-f character on portable-permanent-doc paths (practice-core, rules, memory/active/patterns, principles.md, testing-strategy.md; ADRs are repo-bound and out of scope per PDR-079), with fenced code blocks, inline-code spans, and `(historical reference)` marker lines excluded so the discipline 'moving targets do not belong in permanent docs' (distilled.md) is enforced at write-time without tripping intentional code-block examples or explicit historical citations. PDR-044 names false positives as a design property of the innate layer."
    },
